 London: German midfielder Dietmar Hamann ended a farcical journey around the Premier League clubs of England?s north-west by joining Manchester City on Wednesday. Hamann signed for Bolton Wanderers earlier this month before changing his mind. He officially left Liverpool for Bolton on Tuesday before tying up his switch to City 24 hours later. The 32-year-old has joined on a free transfer and signed a two-year contract with the Blues.

 Paris: Liverpool?s Djibril Cisse joined Marseille on a year-ong loan deal with an option for a permanent transfer on Wednesday. The 24-year-old Frenchman, who broke his leg against China on June 7, has arrived in Marseille with his family, according to a statement on the team?s website. He won?t ba able to play till October.

